#====== Structure of work directories 
#
# Project/
# |   stage00.structure/
# |   |   iter00/
# |   |   |   events/
# |   |   |   |   C202411201443A/
# |   |   |   |   |   DATA/, DATABASES_MPI/, SEM/
# |   |   |   |   |   slurm/: forward.job, misfit.job, ...
# |   |   |   |   |   misfit/:   misfit.h5, grid_search.txt, ...
# |   |   |   |   |   output_forward/
# |   |   |   |   |   output_kernel/:
# |   |   |   |   |   output_perturb_dvp,dvs/: forward simulation with perturbed models (e.g. model_dvp,dvs)
# |   |   |   |   C202006211907A/
# |   |   |   |   | ...
# |   |   |   model_initial/: proc*_reg1_vpv,vph,...bin
# |   |   |   kernel_sum/: sum of event kernels (with source/receiver masks), 
# |   |   |                and reduced to specific model of anisotropy, e.g. TISO
# |   |   |   kernel_precond/: preconditioned kernel (e.g. smoothing, spatial weighting)
# |   |   |   dmodel/: search direction based on non-linear CG, and scaled to certain amplitude 
# |   |   |   model_perturb_dvp,dvs,.../: model perturbed by the (subspaces of) search direction
# |   |   |   line_search/
# |   |   |   model_updated/
#
#====== Basic workflow:
#
#   Note: [***_job] is a slurm job
#
#   [mesh_job] create mesh with initial model
#
#   for each event:
#     [forward_job] forward simulation
#     [misfit_job]  measure misfit, get adjoint source
#     [kernel_job]  kernel simulation, get model gradients (e.g. rho_, cijkl_kernel)
#
#   [kernel_mask_sum_job] sum event kernels with source/receiver masks
#   [kernel_precond_job] preconditioning with smoothing, spatial weighting, etc.
#   [dmodel_job] get search direction based on non-linear CG, and scaled to certain amplitude 
#   [model_perturb_job] perturb model parameters along some chosen search directions in dmodel (e.g. dVp, dVs)
#   [mesh_perturb_job] create meshes for perturbed models
#  
#   for each event:
#     [perturb_job] forward simulation for perturbed models
#     [search_job] grid search through a range of step lengths
#
#   [model_update_job] sum up grid search results from each event to get step length, and update model parameters
#

